{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01J7kVf7B35HveqcDgLnPtRp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working correctly. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Resources created:**\n\n1. **`es-tls` Secret** (namespace: `elasticsearch`) — a self-signed TLS certificate for `es.example.com`, generated using the existing `openssl-toolbox` pod.\n\n2. **`es-https-ingress` Ingress** (namespace: `elasticsearch`) — routes `es.example.com` to the `es-http:9200` ClusterIP service using the `nginx` ingress class, with:\n   - `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: \"true\"` and `force-ssl-redirect: \"true\"` to block plain HTTP\n   - TLS termination using the `es-tls` secret\n\n**Verification results:**\n- Plain HTTP (`http://es.example.com`) → `308 Permanent Redirect` to HTTPS (does not serve content)\n- HTTPS (`https://es.example.com`) → `200 OK` with a valid Elasticsearch response\n- Cluster health: **green**, all 3 nodes healthy"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":292,"cache_read_input_tokens":33026,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":292},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1f802362-8b3f-4009-9f32-77d44e618260","uuid":"4e97c52c-689e-42c1-89d5-410574fda8c3","request_id":"req_011CcLGKSoohNGdvyVjtY5ee"}
